name: Robinson Crusoe
description: Robinson Crusoe, as a young and impulsive wanderer, defied his parents and went to sea. He was involved in a series of violent storms at sea and was warned by the captain that he should not be a seafaring man. Ashamed to go home, Crusoe boarded another ship and returned from a successful trip to Africa

name: The Life and Opinions of Tristram
description: Tristram Shandy set the stage for experimental literature. It was perhaps the first stream-of-consciousness narrative a style later adopted by James Joyce. Sterne exploration of what constitutes a novel, and of the relationship between author and reader had a big influence on writers like Virginia Woolf
